WEBVTT

00:06.136 --> 00:09.835
[ Josh Johnson x Vanyo's
"Look Alive" plays ]

00:09.879 --> 00:12.577
Meredith: In 2019,
the World Health Organization

00:12.621 --> 00:14.623
officially recognized burnout

00:14.666 --> 00:17.060
in its International
Classification of Diseases.

00:17.104 --> 00:18.322
Chief Bailey,
everything okay?

00:18.366 --> 00:19.584
♪ Son of my father

00:19.628 --> 00:22.457
I'm just, um, waiting
to get my smoothie.

00:22.500 --> 00:25.460
Um, but I was gonna
get your smoothie.

00:25.503 --> 00:27.679
Not today.
Today, I'm getting it myself,

00:27.723 --> 00:30.378
'cause I can't bring myself

00:30.421 --> 00:33.424
to go into that
depressing building.

00:33.468 --> 00:35.339
Can I help
in any way?

00:35.383 --> 00:37.298
Yeah,
just leave me alone.

00:37.341 --> 00:39.952
Studies show that doctors
who report signs of burnout

00:39.996 --> 00:42.042
have enlarged amygdalas,

00:42.085 --> 00:45.262
the area in the brain that
regulates fear and aggression.

00:45.306 --> 00:46.742
If that's how you speak
to your residents,

00:46.785 --> 00:48.744
no wonder
we are on probation.

00:48.787 --> 00:50.441
Catherine --
In your office.

00:50.485 --> 00:52.704
Now.

00:52.748 --> 00:55.620
But burnout isn't
an academic exercise.

00:55.664 --> 00:58.623
It's an all-consuming,
systemic condition.

00:58.667 --> 01:02.192
It's your entire body sending
you one clear message.

01:02.236 --> 01:03.628
You know what,
why don't you go ahead,

01:03.672 --> 01:04.673
and I'll take them
to daycare.

01:04.716 --> 01:07.632
Here, give me this.Oh. Thank you.

01:07.676 --> 01:08.851
You sure you're ready?

01:08.894 --> 01:10.157
I'm cleared for surgery.
I'm feeling good.

01:10.200 --> 01:11.897
I'm just a little...slow.

01:11.941 --> 01:13.508
Okay.
Alright.

01:13.551 --> 01:15.205
Uh, I'll see you in the pit.
Alright, give Daddy hugs.

01:15.249 --> 01:16.250
Okay, bye.
Bye, bye, bye, bye, bye.

01:16.293 --> 01:17.990
Mwah.
Okay.

01:18.034 --> 01:19.079
Hey! Look at you.

01:19.122 --> 01:20.558
My little cowboy.

01:20.602 --> 01:23.213
I'm not a cowboy.
I'm a girl.

01:23.257 --> 01:24.823
Okay. Alright.
Cowgirl.

01:24.867 --> 01:27.739
No.
I'm just a girl, silly.

01:27.783 --> 01:31.134
No, honey, you're a boy.

01:31.178 --> 01:33.615
This is just
a cowgirl costume.

01:33.658 --> 01:35.138
Right?
It's pretend, remember?

01:35.182 --> 01:36.531
Oh.
Okay.

01:36.574 --> 01:37.749
Alright.
I'll see you in there.

01:37.793 --> 01:39.142
Bye.Come on --
Come with me.

01:39.186 --> 01:40.491
Whoop.
Let's go this way.

01:40.535 --> 01:42.363
Something has to change,

01:42.406 --> 01:44.539
and it has to change now.

01:44.582 --> 01:47.324
♪ Light the fire, let it rise

01:47.368 --> 01:49.413
If the surgery program
loses its accreditation,

01:49.457 --> 01:50.675
there's no guarantee
that we'll find

01:50.719 --> 01:52.329
another residency spot
somewhere else.

01:52.373 --> 01:53.504
I don't think
that's gonna happen.

01:53.548 --> 01:54.636
Well, and even if we do,

01:54.679 --> 01:56.377
it might not be
a surgical residency.

01:56.420 --> 01:58.335
We might have to switch
to something else.

01:58.379 --> 02:00.120
Like family medicine.

02:00.163 --> 02:01.599
It's my first day back.

02:01.643 --> 02:03.166
Would you please consider
shutting up?

02:03.210 --> 02:05.125
[ Elevator bell dings ]

02:05.168 --> 02:15.004
♪♪

02:15.047 --> 02:18.007
♪ Light the fire, let it rise

02:18.050 --> 02:19.139
[ Elevator bell dings ]

02:19.182 --> 02:22.533
♪ Burn the life into your eyes

02:22.577 --> 02:25.188
♪ Ooh

02:25.232 --> 02:27.190
Well, that was awkward.

02:27.234 --> 02:29.801
♪ So, look alive, look alive

02:31.325 --> 02:33.762
I have spent years
rebranding this organization

02:33.805 --> 02:36.765
into something respectable
that bears my name.

02:36.808 --> 02:40.029
I'm not going to let
my entire legacy shrivel and die

02:40.072 --> 02:43.206
because one hospital
can't get its crap together.

02:43.250 --> 02:44.816
Well, don't you think
that's a little extreme?

02:44.860 --> 02:46.688
The Medical
Accreditation Council

02:46.731 --> 02:49.473
has inquired about visiting
20 different

02:49.517 --> 02:51.997
Fox Foundation hospitals
as of this morning.

02:52.041 --> 02:53.260
With all due respect,
Catherine,

02:53.303 --> 02:54.565
you supported
the Webber method --

02:54.609 --> 02:56.263
Are we here
to point fingers

02:56.306 --> 02:58.308
or are we here
to solve problems?

02:58.352 --> 03:01.398
[ Indistinct conversation ]

03:01.442 --> 03:02.965
Woman on PA: Dr. Lawrence
to the NICU.

03:03.008 --> 03:04.662
Dr. Lawrence to the NICU.

03:04.706 --> 03:06.229
How long have they
been in there?

03:06.273 --> 03:08.231
Well, I've been here
10 minutes,

03:08.275 --> 03:10.755
and she hasn't let either
of them get a word in.

03:10.799 --> 03:13.497
I need to tell Bailey that
my fellow quit this morning.

03:13.541 --> 03:14.803
Makes sense.

03:14.846 --> 03:18.110
People start to feel
the ship sink, they jump.

03:18.154 --> 03:20.330
Oh, my God. Are you still
considering taking that offer?

03:20.374 --> 03:22.985
I made my decision before I knew
about this probation.

03:23.028 --> 03:24.595
Tell Nick that
you've changed your mind.

03:24.639 --> 03:25.640
It isn't about Nick.

03:27.076 --> 03:28.251
Not just about Nick.

03:28.295 --> 03:29.600
Fine.
Congratulations.

03:29.644 --> 03:31.341
I have a presentation.

03:31.385 --> 03:34.214
Some of us are loyal
and want to save this place.

03:35.302 --> 03:36.607
She'll get over it.
Everyone will.

03:36.651 --> 03:39.088
And I will come visit you.
I am pro-Minnesota.

03:39.131 --> 03:40.394
You are
pro-sex in Minnesota.

03:40.437 --> 03:43.484
Well, well.
How far the mighty have fallen.

03:43.527 --> 03:45.399
What the hell did you all
do to this place?

03:45.442 --> 03:47.314
Probation?
Really?

03:47.357 --> 03:49.011
You've always known
how to make an entrance.

03:49.054 --> 03:51.274
[ Chuckles ]
Ooh.

03:58.063 --> 03:59.500
Trinity Lab's "HeartPatch"

03:59.543 --> 04:01.893
can be placed on
a patient's arm or chest,

04:01.937 --> 04:05.114
and within seconds, will
continuously transmit ECG,

04:05.157 --> 04:07.072
respiratory rate,
and oxygen saturation

04:07.116 --> 04:08.770
right to an app on your phone.

04:08.813 --> 04:11.381
You get instant monitoring of
your patient

04:11.425 --> 04:12.991
while you're out doing rounds,
brushing your teeth --

04:13.035 --> 04:14.428
hell, you know what,

04:14.471 --> 04:15.690
you could even check them
on the golf course.

04:15.733 --> 04:17.474
[ Laughter ]

04:17.518 --> 04:20.695
Phase III results rival the gold
standard telemetry monitors.

04:20.738 --> 04:23.175
And Grey-Sloan could be
at the forefront

04:23.219 --> 04:24.481
of this cutting-edge
technology.

04:24.525 --> 04:26.353
So, anybody has questions,
I'm here,

04:26.396 --> 04:27.702
and don't forget,
we got donuts.

04:27.745 --> 04:29.269
[ Laughter ]

04:29.312 --> 04:31.706
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:31.749 --> 04:32.968
Hey.

04:33.011 --> 04:34.535
Thanks for the coffee.

04:34.578 --> 04:36.058
I like that suit.
That's nice.

04:36.101 --> 04:37.451
Yeah, yeah.

04:37.494 --> 04:39.191
I got to look sharp
for my Seattle Pres

04:39.235 --> 04:41.106
and St. Joseph's pitches
this afternoon.

04:41.150 --> 04:42.325
You know, we should
try these patches

04:42.369 --> 04:44.196
on a couple of
our patients today.

04:44.240 --> 04:45.546
Richard said that we needed to

04:45.589 --> 04:47.417
improve our tech
and "modernize."

04:47.461 --> 04:48.853
So...

04:48.897 --> 04:50.507
Really?

04:50.551 --> 04:51.639
Absolutely.

04:51.682 --> 04:52.901
Stay right here.

04:52.944 --> 04:54.163
I'll grab a few samples.

04:59.864 --> 05:01.083
Hey.

05:01.126 --> 05:02.432
What are you doing here?

05:02.476 --> 05:03.781
Snickerdoodles.

05:03.825 --> 05:06.175
My sister baked them
and insisted I bring you some.

05:06.218 --> 05:07.698
Oh, wow.
That's so nice.

05:07.742 --> 05:10.527
Yeah, well, my office is walking
distance, so it wasn't --

05:10.571 --> 05:12.050
Oh, you're talking about
her making the cookies.

05:12.094 --> 05:13.400
[ Chuckles ]
Yes.

05:13.443 --> 05:15.837
But the delivery service
is also appreciated.

05:15.880 --> 05:16.968
How's Laura?
She's good,

05:17.012 --> 05:18.361
but I just heard about

05:18.405 --> 05:20.232
the residency program
getting shut down.

05:20.276 --> 05:21.538
Am I gonna need to find her
a new hospital?

05:21.582 --> 05:23.235
It is not shut down.

05:23.279 --> 05:25.934
It's on probation, and it's just
the surgical residency program.

05:25.977 --> 05:27.675
Oh, okay, great.
So I'll just make sure

05:27.718 --> 05:30.373
the paramedics don't send me
here if I get hit by a car.

05:30.417 --> 05:32.854
[ Laughs ] Our attending
surgeons are very good.

05:32.897 --> 05:34.290
Yeah?
Is that why they kicked you out?

05:34.334 --> 05:35.378
[ Laughs ]

05:35.422 --> 05:37.380
Um, I have to get going
to a meeting,

05:37.424 --> 05:38.425
but I'll see you later?

05:38.468 --> 05:39.556
Yes.
Okay.

05:39.600 --> 05:41.689
Okay.

05:41.732 --> 05:44.344
I didn't realize you were still
hanging out with Tad.

05:44.387 --> 05:46.520
It's Todd, and yes.

05:46.563 --> 05:47.999
He brought me
cookies.

05:48.043 --> 05:49.174
Because he's nice.

05:49.218 --> 05:51.655
How thoughtful.
[ Chuckles ]

05:51.699 --> 05:53.309
What's so funny?

05:53.353 --> 05:55.442
Nothing. I just see how hard
you're trying to like him.

05:55.485 --> 05:57.357
I want nice
to be my type.

05:57.400 --> 05:59.141
Great.
I support that.

06:00.360 --> 06:04.189
♪♪

06:04.233 --> 06:07.976
[ Indistinct announcement
over PA ]

06:08.019 --> 06:09.673
Hey, so, uh --

06:09.717 --> 06:11.327
So, this morning with Leo...

06:11.371 --> 06:12.894
Yeah, we should figure out
what to do.

06:12.937 --> 06:14.025
What do you mean,
"what to do"?

06:14.069 --> 06:16.811
Well,
he's obviously confused.

06:16.854 --> 06:18.116
We should get a therapist.

06:18.160 --> 06:19.596
I mean, one for him and --
and one for us and --

06:19.640 --> 06:20.815
[ Man screaming ]
-Help! We need --

06:20.858 --> 06:21.816
Oh, wow.

06:21.859 --> 06:24.166
Get a gurney now!

06:24.209 --> 06:25.950
What's his name?
What's his name?

06:25.994 --> 06:27.256
C-Colin.Okay.

06:27.299 --> 06:28.388
Alright, ma'am,
step over here, please.

06:28.431 --> 06:29.737
His name is Colin --
Colin Renfield.

06:29.780 --> 06:32.304
We work together at
an e-tail fulfillment center.

06:32.348 --> 06:35.177
His arm got cut off on the
conveyor belt 20 minutes ago.

06:35.220 --> 06:36.396
Is that the, uh...

06:36.439 --> 06:37.571
His arm.

06:37.614 --> 06:38.702
Owen: Okay,
let's get saline and ice.

06:38.746 --> 06:39.921
Let's get him to Trauma One now.
Let's go.

06:39.964 --> 06:41.879
[ Groaning ]

06:41.923 --> 06:43.533
Is there anything else
you need from me?

06:43.577 --> 06:44.665
No, we're good,
thank you.
Okay, good.

06:44.708 --> 06:45.883
Why don't you wait over here
and we'll --

06:45.927 --> 06:47.972
Oh, God, she's going down!I got her!

06:48.016 --> 06:48.712
Alright,
get the wheelchair.

06:48.756 --> 06:51.149
Alright. Alright.

06:51.193 --> 06:52.716
We got you.

06:58.156 --> 07:00.463
Link: He's a little hypotensive.
Normal sats.

07:00.507 --> 07:01.551
Let's type
and cross him for blood.Colin?

07:01.595 --> 07:03.031
Colin, we're gonna do
a quick X-ray

07:03.074 --> 07:04.336
to assess your injuries,
okay?

07:04.380 --> 07:05.555
Push another 50
of fentanyl.

07:05.599 --> 07:07.209
You can put my arm back on,
right?

07:07.252 --> 07:08.123
We're gonna do
our very best.

07:08.166 --> 07:09.733
Okay? I promise.My wife...

07:09.777 --> 07:11.039
We'll inform her right away.

07:11.082 --> 07:12.954
This is a marathon surgery.
Could be 10 hours.

07:12.997 --> 07:14.303
Are you sure
you're up for it?

07:14.346 --> 07:15.783
No shame calling in
reinforcements.

07:15.826 --> 07:17.741
What reinforcements?

07:17.785 --> 07:19.308
Okay, let's page neuro

07:19.351 --> 07:20.527
and tell the OR
we are on our way.

07:20.570 --> 07:22.050
Let's go.

07:22.093 --> 07:23.617
Heart rate and blood pressure
are improving.

07:23.660 --> 07:25.009
Sorry.

07:25.053 --> 07:26.663
I got...woozy.

07:26.707 --> 07:28.491
It's okay.
You had a vasovagal response.

07:28.535 --> 07:30.667
It could be triggered
by a number of things.

07:30.711 --> 07:33.322
The sight of blood,
emotional distress...

07:33.365 --> 07:35.933
How's Colin?
Can they reattach his arm?

07:35.977 --> 07:37.195
They're still trying
to figure it out.

07:37.239 --> 07:39.459
[ Sighs ]
It was horrifying.

07:39.502 --> 07:42.331
It just keeps replaying in
my head, over and over again.

07:42.374 --> 07:43.854
You saw it happen?

07:43.898 --> 07:45.073
[ Exhales sharply ]

07:45.116 --> 07:46.161
The gears on
the conveyor belt --

07:46.204 --> 07:47.597
they made a terrible noise,

07:47.641 --> 07:50.208
and then
Colin started screaming

07:50.252 --> 07:51.862
and his arm
ripped off his shoulder

07:51.906 --> 07:54.212
and went flying around,

07:54.256 --> 07:55.431
spraying blood everywhere.

07:55.475 --> 07:58.216
It was on the floor,
on the merchandise.

07:58.260 --> 08:00.567
Some of it hit my mouth.

08:00.610 --> 08:02.133
I...

08:02.177 --> 08:03.831
Oh, no,
it's happening again.

08:03.874 --> 08:06.268
Alright. That's alright.
We got you.

08:07.182 --> 08:08.705
I have a woman pregnant

08:08.749 --> 08:10.838
with a transplanted uterus
and her dead husband's sperm,

08:10.881 --> 08:12.535
and she's now
experiencing pain.

08:12.579 --> 08:14.102
I mean, should I
be transferring her

08:14.145 --> 08:15.669
to a hospital that
isn't on probation?

08:15.712 --> 08:17.453
Well, the hospital isn't
on probation.

08:17.497 --> 08:19.324
Just the surgical
residency program.

08:19.368 --> 08:21.196
[ Cellphone swishes ]And also this hospital's
been through much worse.

08:21.239 --> 08:22.589
Okay, that doesn't
make me feel better.

08:22.632 --> 08:24.591
But the transplant
worked?

08:24.634 --> 08:25.853
Tovah's
officially pregnant?

08:25.896 --> 08:27.507
Mm-hmm.
One uterus, two IVF cycles.

08:27.550 --> 08:28.812
She is 11 weeks today.

08:28.856 --> 08:30.510
That's amazing.

08:30.553 --> 08:32.860
So, how much is David Hamilton
offering you?

08:32.903 --> 08:34.165
Sorry.
Oh, come on.

08:34.209 --> 08:35.645
The rumors
are everywhere.

08:35.689 --> 08:37.429
I made so many people angry
by even considering it.

08:37.473 --> 08:38.735
Bailey?

08:38.779 --> 08:40.084
And Richard.[ Elevator bell dings ]

08:40.128 --> 08:42.391
Meredith Grey back in neuro,
pissing people off?

08:42.434 --> 08:44.088
It's like I never left.[ Both chuckle ]

08:44.132 --> 08:46.264
There she is.
My favorite student.

08:46.308 --> 08:47.875
[ Chuckles ]

08:47.918 --> 08:51.574
Hi, Richard.

08:51.618 --> 08:55.186
You need to be trying to save
the program, not sulking.

08:55.230 --> 08:57.101
I am recruiting.

08:57.145 --> 08:59.713
These are résumés for
attending surgeons.

08:59.756 --> 09:01.584
Right now,
you need to be focused

09:01.628 --> 09:03.455
on keeping
the residents.

09:03.499 --> 09:07.111
You know when a program goes on
probation, they panic, and flee,

09:07.155 --> 09:09.723
and we lose
government funding.

09:09.766 --> 09:12.552
Well, they'll stay if we have
enough attendings to teach them.

09:12.595 --> 09:13.944
No, no.

09:13.988 --> 09:16.294
We will not hire
any outside surgeons

09:16.338 --> 09:19.776
until we have assurance that
our residents intend to stay

09:19.820 --> 09:22.736
and plan to give good reviews to
the council's follow-up visit.

09:22.779 --> 09:26.043
[ Sighs ]In fact, you will speak
to every one of them.

09:26.087 --> 09:29.699
Today.
And I will observe.

09:29.743 --> 09:31.571
♪♪

09:31.614 --> 09:33.224
[ Sighs ]

09:33.268 --> 09:34.486
Where are you going?

09:34.530 --> 09:36.619
To line up residents to beg.

09:36.663 --> 09:38.099
Highlight of my year.

09:38.142 --> 09:40.492
[ Grunts ]

09:40.536 --> 09:41.755
[ Sighs ]

09:41.798 --> 09:44.627
Haven't done a full arm
reattachment in years.

09:44.671 --> 09:45.889
I've never done one.

09:45.933 --> 09:47.848
Believe it or not,
this is a career first.

09:47.891 --> 09:50.285
Irrigation.Amelia: Good to see you
back in an OR.

09:50.328 --> 09:51.416
[ Chuckles ]

09:51.460 --> 09:52.766
Are we ready
to reattach an arm?

09:52.809 --> 09:54.681
Edges are all freshened up
and ready to go.

09:54.724 --> 09:56.204
Alright.
Let's make sure we have

09:56.247 --> 09:58.380
plenty of blood product on hand,
and everybody buckle up.

09:58.423 --> 10:00.077
We are going
nerve by nerve,

10:00.121 --> 10:02.036
vessel by vessel,
muscle by muscle.

10:02.079 --> 10:04.299
I think we get the idea.

10:04.342 --> 10:05.430
I'm gonna scrub.

10:05.474 --> 10:07.215
[ Alarm blaring ]

10:07.258 --> 10:09.173
[ Flatlining ]V-fib!

10:09.217 --> 10:11.088
He's lost too much blood.
Push epi.

10:11.132 --> 10:12.263
Starting CPR.

10:12.307 --> 10:13.395
I know we have
a blood shortage,

10:13.438 --> 10:15.266
but call for
another three units!

10:15.310 --> 10:19.183
♪♪

10:19.227 --> 10:20.924
Come on.
Come on!

10:20.968 --> 10:23.100
[ Monitor beeping ]

10:23.144 --> 10:25.581
Okay, back to sinus.

10:25.625 --> 10:29.150
[ Sighs ]

10:29.193 --> 10:30.542
Hell of a first
surgery back.

10:30.586 --> 10:31.805
Owen, you saved his life.

10:31.848 --> 10:33.589
But now he's too unstable
to reattach the arm.

10:33.633 --> 10:36.113
Life before limb.I wanted to save both,
okay?

10:36.157 --> 10:39.290
Let's get him up to the ICU
and prep him for resuscitation.

10:39.334 --> 10:42.380
♪♪

10:42.424 --> 10:44.034
[ Ultrasound warbling ]

10:44.078 --> 10:45.383
That's your baby.Tovah: [ Chuckles ]

10:45.427 --> 10:46.558
Heartbeat's strong.

10:46.602 --> 10:48.038
Oh, my God.[ Chuckles ]

10:48.082 --> 10:49.126
Thank you.

10:49.170 --> 10:50.214
[ Chuckles ]

10:50.258 --> 10:53.783
Hi, baby.
Hi, sweetheart.

10:53.827 --> 10:55.655
[ Sobs ] Sorry.

10:55.698 --> 10:56.960
You don't need to be sorry.

10:57.004 --> 10:58.527
I'm scared.

10:58.570 --> 11:00.442
It's my last embryo,

11:00.485 --> 11:02.749
from the last of
my husband's sperm.

11:02.792 --> 11:04.402
And it's still there.Yeah.

11:04.446 --> 11:06.753
Okay, I'm gonna switch to
Doppler now, Schmitt.

11:06.796 --> 11:08.580
Have a look at
the uterine vessels.

11:08.624 --> 11:10.017
So, if the baby's okay,

11:10.060 --> 11:12.280
why am I feeling all this
pressure in my belly?

11:12.323 --> 11:14.891
That is what we're trying to
figure out, Tovah.

11:14.935 --> 11:18.286
[ Ultrasound warbling ]

11:18.329 --> 11:22.638
Have a look, Schmitt.

11:22.682 --> 11:24.074
Oh.

11:24.118 --> 11:25.206
What? What is it?
Tell me.

11:25.249 --> 11:26.511
It looks like
there's diminished blood

11:26.555 --> 11:28.165
flowing to both sides
of the uterus, Tovah.

11:28.209 --> 11:30.341
Right side looks
a little thrombosed.

11:30.385 --> 11:32.213
It's a-a blood clot.

11:32.256 --> 11:33.736
Oh, no. Oh, God.
But the baby --

11:33.780 --> 11:35.085
The baby is fine, okay?

11:35.129 --> 11:36.347
We just need to order
some more scans.

11:36.391 --> 11:38.175
Alright, let's order an MR angio
right away,

11:38.219 --> 11:39.742
and page Webber and Grey.

11:39.786 --> 11:42.745
I want their eyes on this in
case we need an IR intervention.

11:42.789 --> 11:44.921
Uh, both of them? They're --
They're having a little --

11:44.965 --> 11:46.706
Yeah, I don't care.
I'm not a high-school teacher.

11:46.749 --> 11:48.185
I don't care who's talking
to who and who isn't.

11:48.229 --> 11:49.447
Page Webber and Grey.

11:49.491 --> 11:52.102
Yes.

11:52.146 --> 11:54.148
Okay.
Step at a time, Tovah.

11:54.191 --> 11:56.541
[ Door closes ]

12:02.025 --> 12:03.766
[ Inhales sharply ]

12:03.810 --> 12:05.637
[ Indistinct announcement
over PA ]

12:05.681 --> 12:09.293
[ Monitor beeping ]

12:09.337 --> 12:10.599
How's Colin?

12:10.642 --> 12:12.644
He's okay.

12:12.688 --> 12:15.125
There was a slight complication
in the operating room,

12:15.169 --> 12:16.997
but we were able
to resuscitate him.

12:17.040 --> 12:18.912
Thank God.

12:18.955 --> 12:20.435
And his arm?

12:20.478 --> 12:22.524
At this point,
he's just not stable enough

12:22.567 --> 12:25.309
to withstand a 10-hour surgery
to reattach it.

12:25.353 --> 12:27.529
So, you'll do it later?

12:27.572 --> 12:29.400
Unfortunately,
without blood flow...

12:29.444 --> 12:32.882
[sighs] his arm won't survive
much longer.

12:32.926 --> 12:35.580
This is all my fault.

12:35.624 --> 12:37.147
Yesterday, when I got to work,

12:37.191 --> 12:39.497
I saw that one of the conveyor
belts was acting up again,

12:39.541 --> 12:41.935
but I didn't tell anyone
to fix it.

12:41.978 --> 12:44.459
When I got to work
this morning,

12:44.502 --> 12:47.462
I wasn't paying attention,

12:47.505 --> 12:51.292
and then
he switched it on.

12:51.335 --> 12:52.772
I could have
done something.

12:52.815 --> 12:54.643
I could have stopped this
from even happening.

12:54.686 --> 12:56.776
♪♪

12:56.819 --> 12:58.255
Can I see him?

12:58.299 --> 12:59.604
Of course.

12:59.648 --> 13:07.874
♪♪

13:07.917 --> 13:09.223
Think about
all the military vets

13:09.266 --> 13:11.312
that we've seen
lose limbs in combat,

13:11.355 --> 13:14.576
and they've gone on
to live very full lives.

13:14.619 --> 13:16.578
It's gonna be an adjustment,
but...

13:16.621 --> 13:18.972
♪♪

13:19.015 --> 13:19.842
Wait,
where are you going?

13:19.886 --> 13:20.930
To find that arm.

13:20.974 --> 13:22.714
I think
I can save it.

13:22.758 --> 13:25.326
♪♪

13:25.369 --> 13:28.198
Two rounds of IVF,
11 weeks today, so...

13:28.242 --> 13:29.983
Hey.
Hey.

13:30.026 --> 13:32.420
Um, we already have
a general surgeon.

13:32.463 --> 13:34.552
Oh.
Well, if I'm not needed here.

13:34.596 --> 13:35.684
Yeah, that's a good idea.

13:35.727 --> 13:36.990
Just leave
and that'll fix everything.

13:37.033 --> 13:38.643
You are, and she is.

13:38.687 --> 13:40.558
You're not exactly subtle,
you know that?

13:40.602 --> 13:42.473
Okay,
as delightful as this is,

13:42.517 --> 13:45.346
I have a patient at risk of
losing her uterus and a fetus,

13:45.389 --> 13:47.739
so if we could just
focus up here, please.

13:47.783 --> 13:52.396
[ Computer beeping ]

13:52.440 --> 13:55.573
Damn it. The right outflow
is completely clotted off.

13:55.617 --> 13:58.098
The left side is severely
stenosed, but salvageable.

13:58.141 --> 14:00.448
We could do a fibrinolysis
and dissolve the clot.

14:00.491 --> 14:02.145
Not if you don't want to
kill the fetus.

14:02.189 --> 14:04.669
Well, of course I don't
want to kill the fetus.

14:04.713 --> 14:07.411
We could do a balloon
angioplasty on the left side

14:07.455 --> 14:08.760
and see if that
widens the blood vessel.

14:08.804 --> 14:10.066
Let's prep her for angio.

14:10.110 --> 14:11.720
You don't need
the both of us there.

14:11.763 --> 14:14.027
On a normal case, I wouldn't,
but this isn't a normal case.

14:14.070 --> 14:16.159
Tovah's making medical history.
We all are.

14:16.203 --> 14:17.813
Look,
I don't care what kind of

14:17.857 --> 14:20.033
giant dumpster fire
this hospital is,

14:20.076 --> 14:21.904
I refuse to let Tovah
burn with it.

14:21.948 --> 14:24.689
So, we're all adults here.
Let's act like it.

14:24.733 --> 14:31.174
♪♪

14:31.218 --> 14:35.657
[ Indistinct announcement
over PA ]

14:35.700 --> 14:37.615
The ashes are falling.
Oh!

14:37.659 --> 14:39.269
Hi, Bailey.

14:39.313 --> 14:40.227
H-How are you?

14:40.270 --> 14:41.924
I'm desperate.
I'm in need.

14:41.968 --> 14:43.317
And if I remember correctly,

14:43.360 --> 14:45.188
I've been very good to you
when you were in need.

14:45.232 --> 14:47.669
Do you need
something specific?

14:47.712 --> 14:51.412
I need you back
as a general surgery attending.

14:51.455 --> 14:54.067
And I know how big
an ask this is,

14:54.110 --> 14:57.113
and I wouldn't be coming to you
if I had other options.

14:57.157 --> 15:00.377
You want me to just give up
my OB residency spot a year in?

15:00.421 --> 15:01.988
As soon as the program
is off probation,

15:02.031 --> 15:03.424
you can return to OB.

15:03.467 --> 15:06.035
Okay, and what if they fill
my spot in the meantime?

15:06.079 --> 15:07.428
On average,
I'm having to cancel

15:07.471 --> 15:09.647
seven scheduled surgeries
per day.

15:09.691 --> 15:11.823
That's seven patients
who have to wait.

15:11.867 --> 15:15.436
That's seven surgeries that
residents do not get to assist.

15:15.479 --> 15:18.482
If I had even one more attending
on the schedule,

15:18.526 --> 15:21.659
you, well, I could
cut that number in half.

15:21.703 --> 15:23.139
Bailey --

15:23.183 --> 15:24.575
Please,
don't make me beg.

15:24.619 --> 15:27.274
I don't like it,
and I'm not very good at it.

15:27.317 --> 15:29.102
Do I have to decide
right now?

15:29.145 --> 15:32.757
You have to decide yesterday,
if possible.

15:32.801 --> 15:35.847
This hospital has given you
a lot, Wilson.

15:35.891 --> 15:37.501
♪♪

15:37.545 --> 15:39.547
Hopefully,
you'll return the favor.

15:39.590 --> 15:42.724
♪♪

15:42.767 --> 15:45.857
That little Band-Aid's supposed
to monitor all my vitals?

15:45.901 --> 15:48.817
Heart rhythm, oxygen levels,
respiratory rate.

15:48.860 --> 15:51.037
There is even something to
measure your sleep quality.

15:51.080 --> 15:52.908
Whatever happened to
the good old stethoscope?

15:52.952 --> 15:53.996
[ Chuckles ]

15:54.040 --> 15:55.476
Alright.
Here you go.

15:55.519 --> 15:57.608
Sorry, our Wi-Fi
is not having it today.

15:57.652 --> 15:59.741
Stethoscopes
don't need no Wi-Fi.

15:59.784 --> 16:01.395
[ Tablet beeps ]Maggie: Oh, it's up!

16:01.438 --> 16:04.572
[ Flatlining ]It says he's dead.

16:04.615 --> 16:06.095
-What?
-Huh?

16:06.139 --> 16:08.010
Yeah, it...

16:08.054 --> 16:09.229
Okay, hold on.

16:09.272 --> 16:10.665
Ah!

16:10.708 --> 16:12.623
[ Tablet beeps ]

16:12.667 --> 16:14.451
Try it now.

16:14.495 --> 16:16.105
[ Flatlining ]Oh, no, you're dead, too.

16:16.149 --> 16:18.629
I find that
slightly comforting.

16:18.673 --> 16:23.721
♪♪

16:23.765 --> 16:26.942
You basically re-created
an entire circulatory system

16:26.986 --> 16:28.291
to support the arm.

16:28.335 --> 16:30.206
It's called ex-vivo
limb perfusion.

16:30.250 --> 16:31.860
It was being tested
for military use

16:31.903 --> 16:33.035
when Teddy and I
were in Iraq.

16:33.079 --> 16:34.123
Think it'll work?I hope so.

16:34.167 --> 16:35.516
I'll keep you both
posted.

16:35.559 --> 16:37.213
Thank you.

16:39.694 --> 16:42.131
That's so cool.

16:42.175 --> 16:44.612
Owen, this technique hasn't been
approved for civilian use.

16:44.655 --> 16:46.135
And if it works,
what does it matter?

16:46.179 --> 16:48.442
If the military finds out --Then they will say,

16:48.485 --> 16:50.226
"Congratulations, Dr. Hunt.
You saved an arm."

16:50.270 --> 16:52.054
Do you really want
their attention right now?

16:52.098 --> 16:53.708
I will cross that bridge
if it comes to it.

16:53.751 --> 16:56.624
Oh.
So your plan is to just wing it?

16:56.667 --> 16:59.105
Is that what
you want to do with Leo?

16:59.148 --> 17:00.932
Owen,
this is a big deal.

17:00.976 --> 17:03.370
What happened this morning
is a big deal.

17:03.413 --> 17:05.154
Our son told us
that he's a girl.

17:05.198 --> 17:07.113
Yes, and you immediately said,
"No, you're not."

17:07.156 --> 17:10.203
I know. I'm sorry.
It -- It was a mistake.

17:10.246 --> 17:13.249
We've -- We've let him
wear dresses

17:13.293 --> 17:14.772
and we've laughed
and smiled,

17:14.816 --> 17:18.080
but maybe we should be
paying closer attention.

17:18.124 --> 17:19.429
We can't just wing it.

17:19.473 --> 17:21.214
Think about how
your mom is gonna react.

17:21.257 --> 17:23.433
We need to have a plan so that
we can try and help him.

17:23.477 --> 17:24.869
The only thing that needs help
in this exact moment

17:24.913 --> 17:26.132
is our patient.

17:26.175 --> 17:27.394
So, can you please just go
and check on him

17:27.437 --> 17:29.222
while I try and keep this arm
from dying?

17:29.265 --> 17:30.832
♪♪

17:30.875 --> 17:32.355
[ Sighs ]

17:32.399 --> 17:39.971
♪♪

17:46.239 --> 17:47.240
[ Monitor beeping ]

17:47.283 --> 17:48.371
Four generations
of surgeons.

17:48.415 --> 17:50.547
All students of
Dr. Richard Webber.

17:50.591 --> 17:53.681
Technically, it's three
generations, plus Dr. Webber.

17:55.944 --> 17:58.381
I-I literally don't know
why I'm talking.

17:58.425 --> 17:59.991
You know,
there was a time when

18:00.035 --> 18:01.428
being my student
meant something.

18:01.471 --> 18:03.256
But now,
there's no loyalty.

18:03.299 --> 18:05.214
Spare me the loyalty speech,
please.

18:05.258 --> 18:06.694
In case you're curious,
Schmitt,

18:06.737 --> 18:10.045
Dr. Montgomery was a machine
during her residency.

18:10.089 --> 18:11.438
There was a stretch where

18:11.481 --> 18:13.483
she and Derek Shepherd
were my students.

18:13.527 --> 18:14.832
We're doing this now,
huh?

18:14.876 --> 18:16.921
They did these gauntlets of
back-to-back surgeries

18:16.965 --> 18:18.358
over the course
of several days.

18:18.401 --> 18:21.056
I mean, no sleep,
barely a meal break.

18:21.100 --> 18:22.275
I mean,
it was astonishing.

18:22.318 --> 18:23.711
That's one version
of the story.

18:23.754 --> 18:25.278
Care to elaborate?

18:25.321 --> 18:26.540
Not particularly.

18:26.583 --> 18:28.498
Let's just say that
my memory of that time

18:28.542 --> 18:30.457
isn't quite as romantic
as yours, Dr. Webber.

18:30.500 --> 18:32.285
Well, would you prefer
that I talk about

18:32.328 --> 18:34.200
your residency years instead,
Meredith?

18:34.243 --> 18:37.116
No, I would not.

18:40.206 --> 18:42.991
Of course the HeartPatches
are garbage.

18:43.034 --> 18:44.949
My brother is
a walking pawn shop.

18:44.993 --> 18:46.777
Maybe we got a bad batch.

18:46.821 --> 18:49.128
Or maybe we didn't
apply it properly.

18:49.171 --> 18:51.304
Yeah, you know, somehow,
I doubt that.

18:51.347 --> 18:55.177
Okay.
Let's see.

18:55.221 --> 18:58.354
Hey, your pulse ox is good,
heart rate is good.

18:58.398 --> 19:00.226
Why don't you try
doing something

19:00.269 --> 19:02.271
to increase
your heart rate?

19:04.404 --> 19:07.058
What are you doing?
What are you doing?

19:07.102 --> 19:09.583
I am increasing
my heart rate.

19:09.626 --> 19:11.585
Is it working?

19:11.628 --> 19:13.064
Actually, yeah.

19:13.108 --> 19:14.196
Mm.

19:14.240 --> 19:15.719
[ Monitor beeping ]

19:15.763 --> 19:17.243
[ Flatlining ]

19:17.286 --> 19:19.027
Oh, no.
Oh.

19:19.070 --> 19:21.116
Well,
I know you're not dead.

19:21.160 --> 19:24.337
You wanna stop
and go tell Wendell right now?

19:24.380 --> 19:26.339
Mnh-mnh.

19:26.382 --> 19:29.472
Nope.

19:29.516 --> 19:31.126
[ Door closes ]

19:31.170 --> 19:32.475
[ Coffee pours ]Link: Hey.

19:32.519 --> 19:35.304
If you tell me this coffee's
only for attendings,

19:35.348 --> 19:37.654
I will break the pot
into a thousand pieces.

19:37.698 --> 19:39.874
Okay.
I'm sorry for earlier.

19:39.917 --> 19:41.223
You deserve a nice guy.

19:41.267 --> 19:42.920
It's... [ Sighs ]

19:45.445 --> 19:47.229
Bailey asked me to come back
to general surgery

19:47.273 --> 19:48.535
to save the program.

19:48.578 --> 19:50.450
Wow.

19:50.493 --> 19:52.713
Yeah.

19:52.756 --> 19:54.410
So,
what are you gonna do?

19:54.454 --> 19:56.369
I don't know.
I just --

19:56.412 --> 19:57.892
Can we grab dinner tonight?

19:57.935 --> 20:01.069
I just -- I need to talk this
through over several drinks.

20:01.112 --> 20:02.201
Aren't you going out
with Todd?

20:02.244 --> 20:03.724
Yes, but he doesn't
talk medicine

20:03.767 --> 20:07.249
or accreditation probation,
so can you please just join us?

20:07.293 --> 20:09.773
Unless it's weird.

20:09.817 --> 20:12.515
Nope. Not weird.

20:12.559 --> 20:16.084
I'll do all the pros and cons
of vaginas versus colons.

20:16.127 --> 20:17.825
With the nice guy
you're dating.

20:17.868 --> 20:19.696
Thank you.
Joe's?

20:19.740 --> 20:22.395
Of course.
You're the best.

20:26.137 --> 20:27.400
Oh. Thank you.

20:27.443 --> 20:28.662
Yeah.

20:28.705 --> 20:31.360
So, um,

20:31.404 --> 20:34.450
ooh, what are you gonna tell
Wendell about the patch?

20:34.494 --> 20:36.409
Uh, I'm gonna tell him
the truth.

20:36.452 --> 20:38.367
These don't work.

20:38.411 --> 20:39.890
It's a medical device.

20:39.934 --> 20:41.414
What if Grey-Sloan
bought them?

20:41.457 --> 20:42.415
While on probation?

20:42.458 --> 20:43.590
This place cannot --Whoa!

20:43.633 --> 20:45.287
Maggie, Winston.

20:45.331 --> 20:46.941
What's up, bro?
You never texted me back.

20:46.984 --> 20:48.943
Is your shirt
inside out?

20:48.986 --> 20:50.379
[ Chuckles ]

20:50.423 --> 20:51.554
Yeah, I'm -- I'm just --

20:51.598 --> 20:53.774
Wait, are you gonna
leave us a review?

20:53.817 --> 20:55.645
'Cause, you know I work off
commissions, right?

20:55.689 --> 20:57.430
And, uh, a rave from
a renowned heart surgeon

20:57.473 --> 20:59.388
would definitely
give me a sales bump.

21:00.911 --> 21:02.565
These don't work.

21:02.609 --> 21:05.133
Ah, get out of here.
[ Chuckles ]

21:05.176 --> 21:06.874
What?

21:08.397 --> 21:09.442
Oh, oh, oh.
You know what?

21:09.485 --> 21:11.139
I-I know what
the problem was.

21:11.182 --> 21:13.315
I gave you the beta models
from testing.

21:13.359 --> 21:15.186
No, these --
these are discontinued.

21:15.230 --> 21:16.710
Let me give you
the retail model.

21:16.753 --> 21:18.842
Fully FDA approved.

21:18.886 --> 21:21.236
Okay, yeah,
I guess we could try those.

21:23.456 --> 21:25.675
Right, Winston?

21:25.719 --> 21:27.590
♪♪

21:27.634 --> 21:29.288
Right.

21:29.331 --> 21:30.506
Let's go.

21:30.550 --> 21:33.683
♪♪

21:33.727 --> 21:36.599
[ Monitor beeping ]

21:36.643 --> 21:38.209
Inflating the balloon.

21:38.253 --> 21:39.646
Let's get the stent
ready.

21:39.689 --> 21:42.649
When did it become a thing
that we "owe" the hospital

21:42.692 --> 21:43.867
that we did
our residency at?

21:43.911 --> 21:45.260
You trained at Columbia.

21:45.304 --> 21:46.479
I don't see you
still working there.

21:46.522 --> 21:48.350
I don't think that's
what anyone's saying.

21:48.394 --> 21:49.917
I have earned the right
to spread my wings.

21:49.960 --> 21:51.571
Of course you have.
But it's not just about that.

21:51.614 --> 21:53.268
Amelia told me that
when you had COVID,

21:53.312 --> 21:54.487
this place nearly broke
without you.

21:54.530 --> 21:55.879
100%.

21:55.923 --> 21:57.620
The hospital broke
because of COVID.

21:57.664 --> 21:59.318
And you weren't there to
lead them through it.

21:59.361 --> 22:00.580
I may remember you
as a featherweight

22:00.623 --> 22:02.059
in light blue scrubs,
but apparently,

22:02.103 --> 22:03.365
you've become some sort of
hospital mascot

22:03.409 --> 22:05.149
in the years since then.[ Chuckles ]

22:05.193 --> 22:07.717
Okay,
removing the catheter.

22:10.633 --> 22:13.114
You know that Richard's not mad
because he's losing a surgeon.

22:13.157 --> 22:14.420
I'm not his student
anymore.

22:14.463 --> 22:15.943
You were never
just his student.

22:15.986 --> 22:17.684
[ Alarm beeping ]Fetal decels.

22:17.727 --> 22:19.120
The uterus isn't getting
enough blood flow.

22:19.163 --> 22:21.035
Contrast
and shoot fluoro.

22:21.078 --> 22:24.995
♪♪

22:25.039 --> 22:27.346
That left vessel is
completely clotted off.

22:27.389 --> 22:36.398
♪♪

22:36.442 --> 22:38.226
It's over.

22:38.269 --> 22:41.490
Damn it!
Okay, um...

22:41.534 --> 22:44.319
Let's prep an ex-lap
and remove the uterus and fetus.

22:44.363 --> 22:45.886
Okay, no, no, no.

22:45.929 --> 22:47.366
We can do
a vascular revision.

22:47.409 --> 22:49.106
If we can harvest
the saphenous vein,

22:49.150 --> 22:51.326
we can maybe bypass
the thrombosed vessels

22:51.370 --> 22:52.936
and save the pregnancy
and the uterus.

22:52.980 --> 22:54.851
♪♪

22:54.895 --> 22:56.505
Prep the abdomen
and leg.

22:56.549 --> 22:57.811
We're opening her up,
and Richard,

22:57.854 --> 22:59.160
I swear, if your head's
not in this --

22:59.203 --> 23:00.727
I'm right here.
Let's do it.

23:00.770 --> 23:02.163
Scrubbing in.

23:02.206 --> 23:06.341
♪♪

23:14.480 --> 23:15.872
[ Door opens ]

23:15.916 --> 23:17.178
[ Knock on door ]

23:17.221 --> 23:18.571
Oh, Dr. Wright.

23:18.614 --> 23:20.877
Do come in.

23:20.921 --> 23:23.489
I've heard so many
good things about you.

23:23.532 --> 23:24.577
Wow.
Really?

23:24.620 --> 23:28.276
Yes.
Dr. Bailey is quite the fan.

23:28.319 --> 23:30.887
Well, uh,
the feeling's mutual.

23:30.931 --> 23:33.412
Dr. Wright,
why do you draw?

23:33.455 --> 23:36.327
I mean, I know
you draw every surgery

23:36.371 --> 23:38.112
before you perform it,
but why?

23:38.155 --> 23:39.679
I'm ambitious,
Dr. Bailey.

23:39.722 --> 23:41.637
I always knew
I wanted to be a surgeon,

23:41.681 --> 23:43.596
but it's hard to have
the patience it takes --

23:43.639 --> 23:45.467
doing every step without
getting ahead of yourself.

23:45.511 --> 23:49.036
But when you
draw the body,

23:49.079 --> 23:51.299
I mean, you see the body,
yeah,

23:51.342 --> 23:53.562
but by taking the time
to draw it,

23:53.606 --> 23:57.305
you're telling yourself that
the body's worth your time,

23:57.348 --> 23:59.350
worth taking
a closer look at.

23:59.394 --> 24:01.744
So then, when a body's
on an operating table,

24:01.788 --> 24:04.443
it's -- it's not something
trying to defeat you.

24:04.486 --> 24:07.010
The body's a work of art.

24:13.756 --> 24:14.931
What's this?

24:14.975 --> 24:17.238
Um, it's the, uh, forms

24:17.281 --> 24:20.502
to complete your transfer,
uh, back to the Clinic.

24:20.546 --> 24:22.504
Oh, you mean
from the Clinic?

24:22.548 --> 24:25.072
I called your program director
in Minnesota.

24:25.115 --> 24:27.596
They still haven't
filled your spot.

24:27.640 --> 24:29.598
Miranda.Did I do something wrong?

24:29.642 --> 24:32.819
Quite the opposite.
Your work is stellar.

24:32.862 --> 24:36.344
You are one of
the finest residents

24:36.387 --> 24:38.172
I've had the pleasure
of teaching.

24:38.215 --> 24:40.522
Which is why
you need to leave.

24:40.566 --> 24:42.916
Dr. Bailey, can we have a word
outside, please?

24:42.959 --> 24:45.484
This is my office. If you want
a word, you can have it here.

24:48.399 --> 24:51.228
Dr. Wright, what Dr. Bailey's
trying to say to you --

24:51.272 --> 24:56.233
What I am trying to say is
if I fail to save this program,

24:56.277 --> 24:58.366
which I might
through no fault of my own,

24:58.409 --> 25:00.673
every resident
will be orphaned.

25:00.716 --> 25:04.981
I don't know if you'd be able to
get a spot somewhere else,

25:05.025 --> 25:08.594
and I want to
protect your future.

25:08.637 --> 25:12.772
[ Voice breaking ]
So, please,

25:12.815 --> 25:14.295
go back to Minnesota.

25:14.338 --> 25:17.298
[ Geographer's
"The Reason" plays ]

25:17.341 --> 25:20.214
♪♪

25:20.257 --> 25:24.044
And hey, you can still learn
from Meredith Grey out there.

25:24.087 --> 25:29.136
♪♪

25:29.179 --> 25:31.573
[ Monitor beeping ]

25:31.617 --> 25:35.359
♪♪

25:35.403 --> 25:41.191
♪ What have I become?

25:41.235 --> 25:43.846
Meredith:
Clot scissors, please.

25:43.890 --> 25:48.590
♪ Water on the sun

25:48.634 --> 25:50.549
Cutting the vein.

25:50.592 --> 25:51.724
Levi:
Removing the vein.

25:51.767 --> 25:53.029
Syringe, please.

25:53.073 --> 25:57.033
♪ The bullet in the gun

25:57.077 --> 25:59.601
Let's flush the vein.

25:59.645 --> 26:05.868
♪ The light inside the siren

26:05.912 --> 26:07.348
No leaking.

26:07.391 --> 26:08.915
Perfect.

26:08.958 --> 26:10.569
Here you go, Dr. Webber.

26:10.612 --> 26:13.920
♪ The reason's going
in and out ♪

26:13.963 --> 26:15.922
♪♪

26:15.965 --> 26:17.532
Suture.

26:17.576 --> 26:22.842
♪ Our lonely ghosts
will scream and shout ♪

26:22.885 --> 26:24.670
One more.

26:24.713 --> 26:26.454
There we go.

26:26.497 --> 26:30.110
♪ If they could only
hear me now ♪

26:30.153 --> 26:31.590
I think we're done here.

26:31.633 --> 26:33.417
Okay. Unclamp.

26:33.461 --> 26:35.158
Unclamping.

26:35.202 --> 26:40.424
Sponge stick.♪ They'd leave their chains
upon the ground ♪

26:40.468 --> 26:42.296
♪ 'Cause the reason's
with me now ♪

26:42.339 --> 26:43.645
Blood flow looks good.

26:43.689 --> 26:46.039
No leaks.
I think we did it.

26:46.082 --> 26:48.171
Schmitt, go and get the Doppler
and check the fetal heartbeat.

26:48.215 --> 26:50.304
Levi: Stand by.

26:50.347 --> 26:57.354
♪♪

26:57.398 --> 26:58.834
Schmitt?

26:58.878 --> 27:01.707
[ Monitor beeping ]

27:01.750 --> 27:05.014
♪♪

27:05.058 --> 27:07.016
No.

27:07.060 --> 27:09.453
♪♪

27:09.497 --> 27:12.587
No.

27:12.631 --> 27:13.719
No!

27:13.762 --> 27:16.112
[ Clattering ]

27:24.077 --> 27:26.688
[ Sighs ]

27:26.732 --> 27:28.777
Addison,
I'm so sorry.

27:28.821 --> 27:31.040
[ Exhales sharply ]

27:31.084 --> 27:32.215
Yeah, me, too.

27:34.914 --> 27:38.308
Okay,
let's prep for a D&C.

27:40.659 --> 27:43.139
This looks like
the same model.

27:43.183 --> 27:45.185
It is.
There is no other model.

27:46.969 --> 27:49.015
I don't understand.

27:49.058 --> 27:50.712
I got a loan,
and I bought it.

27:50.756 --> 27:52.540
All of it.

27:52.583 --> 27:54.890
You're saying
it doesn't work?

27:54.934 --> 27:56.718
Look, Winston, if I can't
sell this stuff --

27:56.762 --> 27:58.938
You got a loan?

27:58.981 --> 28:00.809
Yeah, like --
Like, from a bank?

28:00.853 --> 28:03.029
Not from a bank.

28:04.900 --> 28:07.468
How could you
be this stupid?

28:07.511 --> 28:09.470
No, you know what?
How could Ibe this stupid?

28:09.513 --> 28:11.559
You said
you had a real job.

28:11.602 --> 28:13.692
You were working on commission.
You lied to me.

28:13.735 --> 28:14.954
It works.

28:14.997 --> 28:17.739
I swear. I-I saw it on
an online presentation.

28:17.783 --> 28:19.306
Oh, my God, dude.

28:19.349 --> 28:20.873
Look,
I saw an opportunity.

28:20.916 --> 28:22.222
Surgeons in the family,

28:22.265 --> 28:23.919
direct connection
to the Fox Foundation.

28:23.963 --> 28:24.833
Look, I put the pieces together,
and I went for it.

28:24.877 --> 28:27.357
How much are you out?

28:27.401 --> 28:28.402
10 grand.

28:28.445 --> 28:29.577
[ Exhales sharply ]

28:29.620 --> 28:31.274
Look, everything I have
is in this.

28:31.318 --> 28:33.102
If you're saying
it doesn't work,

28:33.146 --> 28:36.062
if -- if I can't
sell this stuff...

28:36.105 --> 28:38.238
you have to
help me sell it

28:38.281 --> 28:39.718
or pay back the loan.

28:39.761 --> 28:40.719
Wendell --

28:40.762 --> 28:42.764
If you're my brother,

28:42.808 --> 28:44.853
if we're family,
you will.

28:44.897 --> 28:47.682
You have to help me.

28:47.726 --> 28:48.596
Please.

28:54.471 --> 28:56.909
Teddy: Colin's wife
is half an hour away.

28:56.952 --> 28:58.432
It worked?

28:58.475 --> 28:59.738
Yep.
Toxins are flushing,

28:59.781 --> 29:01.348
arm is looking pink,

29:01.391 --> 29:03.698
and tissue is
oxygenating properly.

29:03.742 --> 29:05.961
That's great news.

29:09.008 --> 29:13.142
Listen, Teddy, I'm not
winging it with Leo, okay?

29:13.186 --> 29:15.188
I'm just -- I thought
this might happen

29:15.231 --> 29:16.798
ever since he started
wearing a tutu, didn't you?

29:16.842 --> 29:18.234
At four?
No.

29:18.278 --> 29:20.280
I thought we were raising a son
who loves dress-up.

29:20.323 --> 29:23.109
Teddy, if Leo says,
"I'm a girl,"

29:23.152 --> 29:24.763
I'm gonna listen.So, that's it?

29:24.806 --> 29:27.461
We're just gonna tell everyone
that Leo's a girl now?

29:27.504 --> 29:28.767
What, before he can even
tie his own shoes?

29:28.810 --> 29:29.898
Maybe? I don't know.

29:29.942 --> 29:31.291
He might change his mind
in two months.

29:31.334 --> 29:33.075
Then we'll just tell everyone
that he's a boy again.

29:33.119 --> 29:34.163
Won't that be
even more confusing?

29:34.207 --> 29:35.643
I don't know, Teddy.

29:35.686 --> 29:37.427
I don't have all the answers,
okay?

29:37.471 --> 29:40.126
I just think we have to
follow his lead.

29:47.089 --> 29:48.743
Meredith Grey.

29:48.787 --> 29:50.440
Catherine, I can't do this
right now.

29:50.484 --> 29:51.920
You would leave this place
right when it --

29:51.964 --> 29:53.574
Catherine --Do not interrupt me!

29:53.617 --> 29:55.228
Please don't talk to her
that way.

29:55.271 --> 29:56.882
You are not her boss,
nor are you mine.

29:56.925 --> 29:57.970
-Boss?
-Excuse you?

29:58.013 --> 29:59.493
This is about honor.

29:59.536 --> 30:01.147
This is about the standing
of this hospital.

30:01.190 --> 30:01.800
Okay, can we not do this?The standing
of this foundation!

30:01.843 --> 30:03.410
Can we just stop?!

30:03.453 --> 30:05.804
For a minute.

30:05.847 --> 30:08.328
A woman just
lost her pregnancy.

30:08.371 --> 30:10.460
A pregnancy
that she fought for

30:10.504 --> 30:12.288
with everything that she had
left in her body.

30:12.332 --> 30:14.856
Through grief, through pain,
through loss.

30:14.900 --> 30:17.598
She fought
and she lost her pregnancy.

30:17.641 --> 30:21.167
Can we just take a moment
[Chuckles] and honor her?

30:21.210 --> 30:23.647
Just a moment
to honor Tovah?

30:23.691 --> 30:33.179
♪♪

30:38.358 --> 30:41.491
[ Luke Sital-Singh's
"Turning Tides" plays ]

30:41.535 --> 30:44.103
Mrs. Renfield, your husband has
been through major trauma.

30:44.146 --> 30:46.366
Will he be okay?

30:46.409 --> 30:48.542
He has to be okay.

30:48.585 --> 30:50.370
We've given him
some time to stabilize,

30:50.413 --> 30:51.893
but we've scheduled
his surgery

30:51.937 --> 30:53.155
for first thing
tomorrow morning.

30:53.199 --> 30:54.809
It was touch and go,
but in the end,

30:54.853 --> 30:56.245
we were able to save it.

30:56.289 --> 30:57.551
We're gonna
reattach the arm.

30:57.594 --> 30:59.074
Thank God.

30:59.118 --> 31:01.424
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

31:01.468 --> 31:03.557
♪ Maybe this time

31:03.600 --> 31:08.127
♪ There'll be more to say

31:08.170 --> 31:10.520
♪ It'll all have changed

31:10.564 --> 31:12.348
[ Crying ]I'm so sorry, Tovah.

31:12.392 --> 31:16.222
We'll try again,
just as soon as we can.

31:16.265 --> 31:18.615
[ Sobbing ]

31:18.659 --> 31:21.967
♪ I've got a worried mind

31:22.010 --> 31:25.405
♪ Maybe half the time

31:25.448 --> 31:27.755
When my grandfather died,

31:27.798 --> 31:30.323
our rabbi taught me
the Mourner's Kaddish.

31:30.366 --> 31:32.542
♪♪

31:32.586 --> 31:35.894
I know it's not really
the normal time to say it,

31:35.937 --> 31:38.940
but it's always helped me.

31:38.984 --> 31:41.943
[ Sobbing ]

31:41.987 --> 31:45.773
♪ And I get hurt

31:45.816 --> 31:47.949
♪ But I get by

31:47.993 --> 31:56.218
Yitgadal v'yitkadash sh'mei
raba b'alma di-v'ra

31:56.262 --> 31:59.656
chirutei,
v'yamlich malchutei

31:59.700 --> 32:04.270
b'chayeichon uvyomeichon
uvchayei,

32:04.313 --> 32:09.231
d'chol beit yisrael,

32:09.275 --> 32:13.844
ba'agala uvizman kariv.

32:13.888 --> 32:15.977
V'im'ru.
Amen.

32:16.021 --> 32:18.371
Amen.
[ Sobbing ]

32:18.414 --> 32:21.591
♪ Like an unheard prayer

32:21.635 --> 32:23.854
♪ But it's alright

32:23.898 --> 32:28.859
♪ If we just hold on tight

32:28.903 --> 32:32.037
♪ They'll be wearing gold

32:32.080 --> 32:34.953
♪ When my story's told

32:34.996 --> 32:37.999
♪ I love

32:38.043 --> 32:40.045
I feel like I failed her.

32:40.088 --> 32:42.569
Her uterus is still intact.

32:42.612 --> 32:43.657
She can try again.

32:43.700 --> 32:45.572
Yeah,
but not with her husband.

32:45.615 --> 32:47.835
♪ Can someone slow
the turning tides ♪

32:47.878 --> 32:50.838
You really don't remember
your residency fondly?

32:50.881 --> 32:52.013
[ Chuckles ]

32:52.057 --> 32:53.884
Do you?

32:53.928 --> 32:54.885
Oh, come on, Richard.

32:54.929 --> 32:56.713
You changed my life.
Okay?

32:56.757 --> 32:59.542
But I remember pain.

32:59.586 --> 33:01.022
I remember insomnia.

33:01.066 --> 33:02.589
I remember
bullying attendings.

33:02.632 --> 33:06.158
I remember learning
to treat patients

33:06.201 --> 33:08.769
as wins and losses
instead of people.

33:08.812 --> 33:12.251
Took me years
to unlearn that.

33:12.294 --> 33:15.036
I mean, people haven't
complained before.

33:15.080 --> 33:16.342
I mean, not like this.

33:16.385 --> 33:17.647
Come on.

33:17.691 --> 33:18.735
We couldn't complain.

33:18.779 --> 33:20.041
I couldn't complain.

33:20.085 --> 33:21.390
The surgery world's small.

33:21.434 --> 33:22.435
If you complain,
you lose your spot,

33:22.478 --> 33:23.827
and you never get it back.

33:23.871 --> 33:26.656
That was the culture,
and you know it, Richard.

33:26.700 --> 33:30.051
Look, you know,
you are trying to save

33:30.095 --> 33:32.358
a version of the program
that is old.

33:32.401 --> 33:34.534
It's broken, alright?

33:34.577 --> 33:37.058
You gotta stop with
the reminiscing about the past

33:37.102 --> 33:39.365
and look to the future.

33:39.408 --> 33:41.193
What's the new way
to train surgeons?

33:41.236 --> 33:43.369
I tried that.
It got us shut down.

33:43.412 --> 33:46.372
Well...try again.

33:46.415 --> 33:49.070
♪ Ooh

33:49.114 --> 33:54.206
♪ Oh, I won't be far behind

33:54.249 --> 33:57.078
So, if you say yes...

33:57.122 --> 33:59.385
Then I could lose
my OB residency spot.

33:59.428 --> 34:01.517
And if she says no,
then the chief of surgery

34:01.561 --> 34:04.303
asked her for a favor,
and she was like, "Nah."

34:04.346 --> 34:07.306
Got it.
So, it's a Hobson's choice.

34:07.349 --> 34:09.090
Mm.

34:09.134 --> 34:10.526
When you're offered
a choice

34:10.570 --> 34:12.224
and there's really
only one option.

34:12.267 --> 34:14.269
Oh.
[ Chuckles ]

34:14.313 --> 34:16.663
When I was in grad school,
I told my dissertation chair

34:16.706 --> 34:18.752
that I wanted to
study the impact

34:18.795 --> 34:20.884
of climate change
on global migration.

34:20.928 --> 34:22.843
So, in addition to
environmental science,

34:22.886 --> 34:26.847
it would involve public policy,
sociology, and geography.

34:26.890 --> 34:29.067
Is this story your way of
telling us you have a PhD?

34:29.110 --> 34:31.417
I already knew that, but isn't
that what you studied?

34:31.460 --> 34:33.245
Yeah.
I decided to go for it.

34:33.288 --> 34:35.769
I basically lived at
the library, but I did it,

34:35.812 --> 34:37.901
and I didn't have to
spend a year of my life

34:37.945 --> 34:40.948
studying the atmospheric
effect of moss,

34:40.991 --> 34:42.732
which is what
she wanted me to do.

34:42.776 --> 34:44.125
I mean,
no offense to moss,

34:44.169 --> 34:48.129
but point is,
maybe you could do both.

34:48.173 --> 34:49.696
I mean, I know
it'd be more work,

34:49.739 --> 34:53.003
but if that's what you want,
I say go for it.

34:53.047 --> 34:55.963
♪♪

34:56.006 --> 34:57.225
What he said.

34:57.269 --> 34:58.531
Yeah.

34:58.574 --> 35:00.533
Keep your residency
and moonlight for Bailey.

35:00.576 --> 35:01.795
I've seen you
handle worse.

35:01.838 --> 35:03.666
But I have a baby.
I have a tiny human.

35:03.710 --> 35:05.364
Right.It's only for a few weeks,

35:05.407 --> 35:07.061
or a few months,

35:07.105 --> 35:10.673
and, uh, I can help you out
with Luna.

35:10.717 --> 35:13.937
♪♪

35:13.981 --> 35:15.896
I could help
with Luna, too.

35:15.939 --> 35:17.158
♪♪

35:17.202 --> 35:18.377
Yeah, no, scratch that.

35:18.420 --> 35:19.378
Next round's on me,
though.

35:19.421 --> 35:20.770
-Okay.
-Okay.

35:20.814 --> 35:30.040
♪♪

35:34.349 --> 35:35.437
Hey.

35:35.481 --> 35:37.047
Hey.

35:43.402 --> 35:46.013
I want Leo
to be happy.

35:46.056 --> 35:49.625
I never wanted anything but
happiness for our kids.

35:49.669 --> 35:51.888
But I just, uh...

35:54.543 --> 35:56.458
I don't want to mess this up,

35:56.502 --> 36:00.288
and it just feels like there are
a million ways to get it wrong,

36:00.332 --> 36:03.422
and if Leo were 10, then we'd be
having a different conversation,

36:03.465 --> 36:07.600
but he's not, and, you know,
neither one of us

36:07.643 --> 36:11.647
has done enough research
to know how to handle this.

36:11.691 --> 36:15.303
And...

36:15.347 --> 36:18.306
[ Sighs ]

36:18.350 --> 36:22.745
I want to get it right,
and going all-in now,

36:22.789 --> 36:25.661
it just -- it doesn't
seem right, Owen.

36:29.709 --> 36:33.539
Hey, you remember when
Leo said that he was an owl?

36:35.802 --> 36:38.065
Did you feel the need
to, you know,

36:38.108 --> 36:40.198
call him silly
and correct him?

36:40.241 --> 36:41.764
[ Sighs ]

36:41.808 --> 36:43.331
No.
No.

36:43.375 --> 36:45.942
No, you just loved him.

36:45.986 --> 36:47.292
You just let him explore.

36:49.337 --> 36:52.297
Let's just love Leo,
okay?

36:52.340 --> 36:54.647
Let's listen
when he tells us who he is.

36:54.690 --> 36:56.779
It's more complicated
than that.

36:56.823 --> 36:59.565
Yeah. Yeah.
It is.

36:59.608 --> 37:01.306
Then let's get a therapist.

37:01.349 --> 37:03.308
But for us.

37:03.351 --> 37:04.831
For us, not for Leo.

37:04.874 --> 37:06.354
I'm not correcting Leo.

37:06.398 --> 37:11.577
I'm not telling Leo that there
is something wrong with Leo.

37:11.620 --> 37:14.188
Let's not be
our kid's first bully.

37:14.232 --> 37:15.972
Yeah,
I agree with all of that.

37:16.016 --> 37:17.757
I-I just...

37:17.800 --> 37:19.237
[ Sighs ]

37:19.280 --> 37:22.675
What if we don't agree
on the approach?

37:22.718 --> 37:26.113
♪♪

37:26.156 --> 37:28.681
Honestly?

37:28.724 --> 37:30.160
Honestly, I don't know.

37:30.204 --> 37:33.773
♪♪

37:33.816 --> 37:36.123
Therapy it is.

37:36.166 --> 37:37.733
Yeah.

37:37.777 --> 37:44.958
♪♪

37:45.001 --> 37:52.226
♪♪

37:52.270 --> 37:59.407
♪♪

37:59.451 --> 38:01.757
I was in pain

38:01.801 --> 38:03.106
when you came to see me.

38:03.150 --> 38:05.413
You dumped me
and told me to go away.

38:05.457 --> 38:08.242
I know. I did.

38:08.286 --> 38:11.027
But...

38:11.071 --> 38:14.030
when you were in pain,
I kept showing up.

38:14.074 --> 38:15.467
[ Elevator bell dings ]

38:15.510 --> 38:17.730
I guess that's the difference
between me and you.

38:17.773 --> 38:23.170
♪♪

38:23.213 --> 38:28.567
♪♪

38:28.610 --> 38:29.829
[ Door opens ]

38:32.571 --> 38:35.878
Um, I-I've arranged
a phone call for us

38:35.922 --> 38:37.445
with a major consultant

38:37.489 --> 38:40.274
to help us with
a more formalized plan.

38:40.318 --> 38:41.928
Where are you going?

38:41.971 --> 38:44.017
On vacation.
What?

38:44.060 --> 38:47.803
I haven't just taken
a vacation day ever in my life,

38:47.847 --> 38:50.893
and I have
a new little girl at home,

38:50.937 --> 38:54.157
two teenaged boys who haven't
seen both me and Ben

38:54.201 --> 38:56.682
in the same room in months,

38:56.725 --> 38:57.770
and they need me.

38:57.813 --> 38:59.337
This hospital needs you.

38:59.380 --> 39:01.077
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah.

39:01.121 --> 39:03.123
This hospital needs
too much of me.

39:03.166 --> 39:06.692
No, I'm done
being the superhero.

39:06.735 --> 39:09.129
If Meredith Grey can go away,
then so can I.

39:09.172 --> 39:10.391
Miranda --

39:10.435 --> 39:12.480
Catherine,
I respect the hell out of you.

39:12.524 --> 39:13.829
You know I do.

39:13.873 --> 39:15.831
And I know you understand
what it's like

39:15.875 --> 39:19.879
to be a woman at the top of her
field who isn't allowed to rest.

39:19.922 --> 39:23.535
So, I need you to hear me
when I say

39:23.578 --> 39:24.884
I'm not quitting,

39:24.927 --> 39:26.712
I'm not taking a leave

39:26.755 --> 39:28.931
or saying that
I can't handle this job.

39:28.975 --> 39:31.717
I am taking
a vacation...day.

39:31.760 --> 39:32.979
Maybe two.

39:33.022 --> 39:34.459
[ Exhales sharply ]

39:34.502 --> 39:36.156
'Cause I'm no good to you
like this.

39:36.199 --> 39:38.027
♪♪

39:38.071 --> 39:41.553
Put simply, burnout comes from
a deep imbalance.

39:41.596 --> 39:44.425
Too much stress
with too few rewards.

39:44.469 --> 39:46.427
You're exhausted, depleted.

39:46.471 --> 39:47.994
♪ Feel so restless

39:48.037 --> 39:50.823
♪ Feel so out of time

39:50.866 --> 39:54.304
You no longer have patience,
pleasure, or serotonin.

39:54.348 --> 39:56.655
This is the end, unless...

39:56.698 --> 39:58.265
What are you
doing here?

39:58.308 --> 40:00.354
Well, you know what?

40:00.398 --> 40:02.704
I don't even care.
I'm so happy to see you.

40:02.748 --> 40:04.837
No, but ask me.

40:04.880 --> 40:07.274
I have a speech.

40:07.317 --> 40:09.189
Oh. Okay.

40:09.232 --> 40:10.799
Nick,
what are you doing here?

40:10.843 --> 40:12.497
Don't come to Minnesota.

40:12.540 --> 40:14.237
[ Sighs ]

40:14.281 --> 40:15.543
Look,
if you leave right now,

40:15.587 --> 40:17.284
your people won't be okay,
and you won't be okay.

40:17.327 --> 40:18.590
You won't be happy,

40:18.633 --> 40:20.722
and you'll always resent me
just a little bit.

40:20.766 --> 40:22.071
And I know
you have kids.

40:22.115 --> 40:23.551
They're gonna have to
get used to me being around,

40:23.595 --> 40:25.031
but I am gonna
get my own place,

40:25.074 --> 40:26.946
and we are gonna do this thing
the normal way.

40:26.989 --> 40:28.426
You know,
having dinner together

40:28.469 --> 40:30.645
and not having to get on a plane
just to kiss each other.

40:30.689 --> 40:33.518
And look, I have days,
I have tons of personal days,

40:33.561 --> 40:35.563
and I'm taking a few months
and I'm staying here,

40:35.607 --> 40:37.957
and I'm gonna work locum tenens
at Grey-Sloan,

40:38.000 --> 40:40.525
and we can be together.

40:40.568 --> 40:42.091
Here.

40:42.135 --> 40:44.877
♪♪

40:44.920 --> 40:46.705
I have the right to leave.

40:46.748 --> 40:49.359
I've earned
the right to leave.

40:49.403 --> 40:51.579
Other people from
my residency class,

40:51.623 --> 40:53.755
they left and took
other opportunities.

40:53.799 --> 40:56.018
I stayed. I worked.
I researched.

40:56.062 --> 40:59.108
I won awards
for that place.

40:59.152 --> 41:02.590
I did everything that was
expected of me, and then some.

41:02.634 --> 41:05.550
And now, if I want to leave,
I'm considered disloyal?

41:05.593 --> 41:08.466
It's ridiculous.
It's absurd.

41:08.509 --> 41:17.126
♪♪

41:17.170 --> 41:18.519
You know what else it is?

41:18.563 --> 41:22.392
It's my decision,
and I've made my decision.

41:22.436 --> 41:25.526
So this is all
very patronizing.

41:25.570 --> 41:31.445
♪ If you think you were wrong

41:31.489 --> 41:34.753
♪ Every time that
your eyes meet mine ♪

41:34.796 --> 41:36.929
♪ I feel unsteady

41:36.972 --> 41:40.062
Okay.
[ Scoffs ]

41:40.106 --> 41:42.804
I-I wasn't suggesting
we stay here forever.

41:42.848 --> 41:45.720
I'm suggesting we stay long
enough to save the program.

41:45.764 --> 41:46.939
And then
we can go to Minnesota.

41:46.982 --> 41:48.854
We can go wherever we want,

41:48.897 --> 41:51.160
because you have absolutely
earned the right to leave.

41:51.204 --> 41:52.771
You couldn't have
led with that?

41:52.814 --> 41:54.729
I thought I had.
I'm sorry.

41:54.773 --> 41:58.951
♪ Ooh

41:58.994 --> 42:00.822
[ Sighs ]

42:00.866 --> 42:03.999
Now you've seen
my angry side.

42:04.043 --> 42:06.480
I'm not gonna lie,
it was kinda scary.

42:06.524 --> 42:07.568
[ Chuckles ]

42:07.612 --> 42:09.570
[ Chuckles ]

42:09.614 --> 42:11.224
♪♪

42:11.267 --> 42:13.531
You turn it into something else

42:13.574 --> 42:15.620
and find your path to recovery.

42:15.663 --> 42:19.972
♪♪

42:20.015 --> 42:21.321
What?

42:21.364 --> 42:24.498
[ Sighs ]

42:24.542 --> 42:26.587
Okay. Fine.

42:26.631 --> 42:28.458
We can stay.

42:28.502 --> 42:32.550
But just for
a little while.

42:32.593 --> 42:35.727
Pick the pieces you want
from your life

42:35.770 --> 42:37.467
and find a new way forward.

42:37.511 --> 42:43.169
♪ We were not ready to fall

43:02.231 --> 43:10.239
♪♪

43:10.283 --> 43:18.247
♪♪

43:18.291 --> 43:26.038
♪♪
